      "content": "<h2>What is Photosynthesis?</h2><p>Photosynthesis is the process by which <strong>green plants, algae, and some bacteria</strong> convert light energy (usually from the sun) into chemical energy stored in glucose. It is one of the most important biological processes on Earth.</p><div class='highlight-box'><strong>Simple Definition:</strong> Photosynthesis = Sun + Water + CO₂ → Glucose + Oxygen</div><h2>The Chemical Equation</h2><p>The overall equation for photosynthesis is:</p><div class='fact-box'><strong>6CO₂ + 6H₂O + Light Energy → C₆H₁₂O₆ + 6O₂</strong><br><br>This means: 6 molecules of carbon dioxide + 6 molecules of water + light energy produces 1 molecule of glucose + 6 molecules of oxygen.</div><h2>Where Does Photosynthesis Occur?</h2><p>Photosynthesis occurs in the <strong>chloroplasts</strong> of plant cells. Chloroplasts contain a green pigment called <strong>chlorophyll</strong>, which absorbs light energy and gives plants their green color.</p><ul><li><strong>Chloroplast:</strong> The organelle where photosynthesis takes place</li><li><strong>Chlorophyll:</strong> Green pigment that captures light energy</li><li><strong>Thylakoids:</strong> Membrane structures inside chloroplasts where light reactions occur</li><li><strong>Stroma:</strong> Fluid-filled space where the Calvin cycle occurs</li></ul><h2>Two Stages of Photosynthesis</h2><h3>Stage 1: Light-Dependent Reactions</h3><p>These reactions occur in the <strong>thylakoid membranes</strong> and require direct sunlight. During this stage:</p><ul><li>Light energy is absorbed by chlorophyll</li><li>Water molecules are split (photolysis)</li><li>Oxygen is released as a byproduct</li><li>ATP and NADPH are produced for use in Stage 2</li></ul><h3>Stage 2: The Calvin Cycle (Light-Independent Reactions)</h3><p>These reactions occur in the <strong>stroma</strong> of the chloroplast. They do NOT directly require light but use the ATP and NADPH from Stage 1:</p><ul><li>CO₂ is fixed (converted) into organic compounds</li><li>Glucose (C₆H₁₂O₆) is produced</li><li>This glucose is used by the plant for energy and growth</li></ul><h2>Factors Affecting Photosynthesis</h2><table><tr><th>Factor</th><th>Effect on Photosynthesis</th></tr><tr><td>Light Intensity</td><td>Higher light = more photosynthesis (up to a limit)</td></tr><tr><td>CO₂ Concentration</td><td>More CO₂ = faster rate of photosynthesis</td></tr><tr><td>Temperature</td><td>Optimal at 25-35°C; too high or low slows it</td></tr><tr><td>Water Availability</td><td>Water shortage stops photosynthesis</td></tr><tr><td>Chlorophyll Amount</td><td>More chlorophyll = more light absorbed</td></tr></table><h2>Why is Photosynthesis Important?</h2><ul><li>🌬️ <strong>Oxygen Production:</strong> All the oxygen in our atmosphere comes from photosynthesis</li><li>🍎 <strong>Food Production:</strong> It is the base of all food chains on Earth</li><li>☁️ <strong>Carbon Cycle:</strong> Helps regulate CO₂ levels in the atmosphere</li><li>⚡ <strong>Energy Flow:</strong> Solar energy is converted to chemical energy for all living things</li></ul><h2>Key Terms to Remember</h2><ul><li><strong>Autotrophs:</strong> Organisms that make their own food (plants)</li><li><strong>Heterotrophs:</strong> Organisms that depend on others for food (animals)</li><li><strong>Photoautotrophs:</strong> Organisms that use light to make food</li></ul><div class='highlight-box'><strong>Remember for Exams:</strong> Photosynthesis happens in CHLOROPLASTS. The green color of plants is due to CHLOROPHYLL. Oxygen is a BYPRODUCT of photosynthesis.</div>",
      "content_hi": "<h2>प्रकाश संश्लेषण क्या है?</h2><p>प्रकाश संश्लेषण वह प्रक्रिया है जिसमें <strong>हरे पौधे, शैवाल और कुछ जीवाणु</strong> सूर्य के प्रकाश की ऊर्जा को ग्लूकोज में संग्रहित रासायनिक ऊर्जा में परिवर्तित करते हैं।</p><div class='highlight-box'><strong>सरल परिभाषा:</strong> प्रकाश + जल + CO₂ → ग्लूकोज + ऑक्सीजन</div><h2>रासायनिक समीकरण</h2><div class='fact-box'><strong>6CO₂ + 6H₂O + प्रकाश ऊर्जा → C₆H₁₂O₆ + 6O₂</strong></div><h2>प्रकाश संश्लेषण कहाँ होता है?</h2><p>प्रकाश संश्लेषण पौधों की कोशिकाओं के <strong>क्लोरोप्लास्ट</strong> में होता है। क्लोरोप्लास्ट में <strong>क्लोरोफिल</strong> नामक हरा वर्णक होता है।</p><h2>परीक्षा के लिए याद रखें</h2><ul><li>प्रकाश संश्लेषण क्लोरोप्लास्ट में होता है</li><li>पौधों का हरा रंग क्लोरोफिल के कारण होता है</li><li>ऑक्सीजन इस प्रक्रिया का उपोत्पाद है</li></ul>"
