      "content": "<h2>Introduction</h2><p>The <strong>French Revolution (1789–1799)</strong> was one of the most significant political and social upheavals in world history. It overthrew the monarchy, established a republic, and had profound effects not just on France but on the entire world.</p><h2>Causes of the French Revolution</h2><h3>1. Social Inequality (The Three Estates)</h3><p>French society was divided into three estates:</p><ul><li><strong>First Estate:</strong> Clergy (less than 1% of population, owned 10% of land)</li><li><strong>Second Estate:</strong> Nobility (about 2%, paid no taxes)</li><li><strong>Third Estate:</strong> Common people (97% of population, paid all taxes)</li></ul><h3>2. Economic Crisis</h3><ul><li>France was bankrupt after wars (including helping American Revolution)</li><li>Poor harvests led to food shortages and starvation</li><li>Heavy taxation on the Third Estate</li></ul><h3>3. Political Causes</h3><ul><li>Weak leadership of <strong>King Louis XVI</strong></li><li>No representation for common people in government</li><li>Inspiration from American Revolution (1776)</li></ul><h3>4. Philosophical Influence</h3><p>The ideas of <strong>Enlightenment philosophers</strong> like Voltaire, Rousseau, and Montesquieu inspired people with concepts of liberty, equality, and fraternity.</p><h2>Major Events</h2><table><tr><th>Date</th><th>Event</th></tr><tr><td>1789, May</td><td>Estates-General convened</td></tr><tr><td>1789, June</td><td>Third Estate forms National Assembly</td></tr><tr><td>1789, July 14</td><td>Storming of the Bastille (Revolution begins)</td></tr><tr><td>1789, August</td><td>Declaration of Rights of Man and Citizen</td></tr><tr><td>1793</td><td>King Louis XVI executed</td></tr><tr><td>1793-94</td><td>Reign of Terror under Robespierre</td></tr><tr><td>1799</td><td>Napoleon Bonaparte takes power</td></tr></table><div class='highlight-box'><strong>Key Slogan:</strong> Liberté, Égalité, Fraternité (Liberty, Equality, Fraternity) — This became the motto of France and inspired revolutions worldwide.</div><h2>Impact of French Revolution</h2><ul><li>🌍 Spread ideas of democracy and human rights worldwide</li><li>⚖️ Abolished feudalism and privileges of nobility</li><li>📜 Inspired many future revolutions in Europe and Latin America</li><li>🗳️ Promoted concept of nationalism</li><li>⚔️ Led to rise of Napoleon Bonaparte</li></ul>",
      "content_hi": "<h2>फ्रांसीसी क्रांति (1789-1799)</h2><p>फ्रांसीसी क्रांति विश्व इतिहास की सबसे महत्वपूर्ण घटनाओं में से एक है जिसने राजतंत्र को उखाड़ फेंका।</p><h2>कारण</h2><ul><li>सामाजिक असमानता - तीन वर्गों में विभाजित समाज</li><li>आर्थिक संकट - भारी कर और अकाल</li><li>राजा लुई XVI का कमजोर शासन</li><li>ज्ञानोदय के दार्शनिकों का प्रभाव</li></ul><h2>मुख्य नारा</h2><div class='highlight-box'>स्वतंत्रता, समानता, बंधुत्व (Liberté, Égalité, Fraternité)</div>"
