      "content": "<h2>Introduction</h2><p>India's struggle for independence from British rule lasted nearly <strong>200 years</strong>, from the First War of Independence in 1857 to finally achieving freedom on <strong>August 15, 1947</strong>.</p><h2>Timeline of Major Events</h2><table><tr><th>Year</th><th>Event</th><th>Significance</th></tr><tr><td>1857</td><td>First War of Independence</td><td>First major uprising against British rule</td></tr><tr><td>1885</td><td>Indian National Congress founded</td><td>First major political organization</td></tr><tr><td>1905</td><td>Partition of Bengal</td><td>Sparked mass protest; Swadeshi Movement</td></tr><tr><td>1919</td><td>Jallianwala Bagh Massacre</td><td>Turned national sentiment against British</td></tr><tr><td>1920-22</td><td>Non-Cooperation Movement</td><td>Gandhi's first mass movement</td></tr><tr><td>1930</td><td>Civil Disobedience / Dandi March</td><td>Salt March by Gandhi</td></tr><tr><td>1942</td><td>Quit India Movement</td><td>'Do or Die' — final push for freedom</td></tr><tr><td>1947</td><td>Independence</td><td>India becomes free on August 15</td></tr></table><h2>Key Leaders</h2><div class='highlight-box'><strong>Mahatma Gandhi</strong> (Father of the Nation)<br>Known for: Non-violent resistance (Satyagraha), Civil Disobedience, Quit India Movement</div><div class='fact-box'><strong>Other Key Leaders:</strong><ul><li>🎯 <strong>Bal Gangadhar Tilak</strong> — \"Swaraj is my birthright\" — Father of Indian Unrest</li><li>🦁 <strong>Subhas Chandra Bose</strong> — Founded INA; \"Jai Hind\" — Netaji</li><li>🌹 <strong>Jawaharlal Nehru</strong> — First Prime Minister; Tryst with Destiny speech</li><li>⚖️ <strong>B.R. Ambedkar</strong> — Father of Indian Constitution</li><li>🔥 <strong>Bhagat Singh</strong> — Revolutionary freedom fighter</li></ul></div><h2>Quick Revision Notes</h2><ul><li>Read the definition and write it once in your own words.</li><li>Make a small table of key facts, formulas, dates, or examples related to Indian Freedom Struggle: Key Events, Leaders and Movements.</li><li>Revise the topic after 24 hours and again before the exam.</li></ul><h2>Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2><ul><li>Do not memorize only headings; understand the reason behind every point.</li><li>Do not mix similar terms, dates, examples, or formulas.</li><li>Do not skip practice questions after reading the explanation.</li></ul><h2>Practice Questions</h2><ol><li>Write a short note on the main idea of this topic.</li><li>List three important facts that can be asked in exams.</li><li>Explain one example in simple language.</li><li>Create five one-line revision points from this article.</li></ol><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>Is this topic important for exams?</h3><p>Yes. This topic is useful for school tests, revision, and competitive exam general awareness depending on the syllabus.</p><h3>How should I revise it quickly?</h3><p>Start with the summary, then revise the table or bullet points, and finally solve two or three practice questions.</p>",
      "content_hi": "<h2>भारतीय स्वतंत्रता संग्राम</h2><p>भारत ने 1857 से 1947 तक लगभग 200 साल की लड़ाई के बाद 15 अगस्त 1947 को स्वतंत्रता प्राप्त की।</p><h2>प्रमुख नेता</h2><ul><li><strong>महात्मा गांधी</strong> - राष्ट्रपिता, अहिंसा के पुजारी</li><li><strong>नेताजी सुभाष चंद्र बोस</strong> - आजाद हिंद फौज</li><li><strong>जवाहरलाल नेहरू</strong> - प्रथम प्रधानमंत्री</li><li><strong>भगत सिंह</strong> - क्रांतिकारी</li></ul>"
