      "content": "<h2>Why Abbreviations Matter?</h2><p>Abbreviations and full forms are asked in almost every competitive exam — SSC, UPSC, Banking, Railway, Police etc. This comprehensive list covers all important ones.</p><h2>Banking & Finance</h2><table><tr><th>Abbreviation</th><th>Full Form</th></tr><tr><td>RBI</td><td>Reserve Bank of India</td></tr><tr><td>NABARD</td><td>National Bank for Agriculture and Rural Development</td></tr><tr><td>SEBI</td><td>Securities and Exchange Board of India</td></tr><tr><td>GDP</td><td>Gross Domestic Product</td></tr><tr><td>GNP</td><td>Gross National Product</td></tr><tr><td>IMF</td><td>International Monetary Fund</td></tr><tr><td>WTO</td><td>World Trade Organization</td></tr><tr><td>ATM</td><td>Automated Teller Machine</td></tr><tr><td>NEFT</td><td>National Electronic Funds Transfer</td></tr><tr><td>RTGS</td><td>Real Time Gross Settlement</td></tr></table><h2>Science & Technology</h2><table><tr><th>Abbreviation</th><th>Full Form</th></tr><tr><td>ISRO</td><td>Indian Space Research Organisation</td></tr><tr><td>NASA</td><td>National Aeronautics and Space Administration</td></tr><tr><td>DNA</td><td>Deoxyribonucleic Acid</td></tr><tr><td>RNA</td><td>Ribonucleic Acid</td></tr><tr><td>CPU</td><td>Central Processing Unit</td></tr><tr><td>RAM</td><td>Random Access Memory</td></tr><tr><td>GPS</td><td>Global Positioning System</td></tr><tr><td>WWW</td><td>World Wide Web</td></tr><tr><td>AI</td><td>Artificial Intelligence</td></tr><tr><td>LASER</td><td>Light Amplification by Stimulated Emission of Radiation</td></tr></table><h2>Government & Politics</h2><table><tr><th>Abbreviation</th><th>Full Form</th></tr><tr><td>UNO</td><td>United Nations Organization</td></tr><tr><td>WHO</td><td>World Health Organization</td></tr><tr><td>UNESCO</td><td>United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization</td></tr><tr><td>UNICEF</td><td>United Nations International Children's Emergency Fund</td></tr><tr><td>IPC</td><td>Indian Penal Code</td></tr><tr><td>CBI</td><td>Central Bureau of Investigation</td></tr><tr><td>RAW</td><td>Research and Analysis Wing</td></tr><tr><td>NDA</td><td>National Defence Academy</td></tr><tr><td>UPSC</td><td>Union Public Service Commission</td></tr><tr><td>SSC</td><td>Staff Selection Commission</td></tr></table><h2>Sports</h2><table><tr><th>Abbreviation</th><th>Full Form</th></tr><tr><td>ICC</td><td>International Cricket Council</td></tr><tr><td>FIFA</td><td>Fédération Internationale de Football Association</td></tr><tr><td>IOC</td><td>International Olympic Committee</td></tr><tr><td>BCCI</td><td>Board of Control for Cricket in India</td></tr><tr><td>IPL</td><td>Indian Premier League</td></tr></table><h2>Quick Revision Notes</h2><ul><li>Read the definition and write it once in your own words.</li><li>Make a small table of key facts, formulas, dates, or examples related to 500+ Important Abbreviations for Competitive Exams (A-Z).</li><li>Revise the topic after 24 hours and again before the exam.</li></ul><h2>Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2><ul><li>Do not memorize only headings; understand the reason behind every point.</li><li>Do not mix similar terms, dates, examples, or formulas.</li><li>Do not skip practice questions after reading the explanation.</li></ul><h2>Practice Questions</h2><ol><li>Write a short note on the main idea of this topic.</li><li>List three important facts that can be asked in exams.</li><li>Explain one example in simple language.</li><li>Create five one-line revision points from this article.</li></ol><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>Is this topic important for exams?</h3><p>Yes. This topic is useful for school tests, revision, and competitive exam general awareness depending on the syllabus.</p><h3>How should I revise it quickly?</h3><p>Start with the summary, then revise the table or bullet points, and finally solve two or three practice questions.</p>",
